<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="605" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[132,775,1229,1333]" pageId="4" pageNumber="605">
ETYMOLOGY. — After the name of a closely-related genus, namely 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handlirsch" authorityYear="1939" box="[132,236,1255,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Bintoniellidae" genus="Bintoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[132,236,1255,1279]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="605">Bintoniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, associated with the prefix ‘para’, i.e. ‘beside’ in Ancient Greek, indicative of the assumed close relationships between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handlirsch" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Bintoniellidae" genus="Bintoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="605">Bintoniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
